We went for happy hour and ordered the goat cheese dip, fingerling potatoes, french onion burger, and the forbidden rice. Goat cheese dip was so so. Fingerling potatoes were very yummy with fried sage and rosemary and a lemon aioli. The french onion burger was AMAZING and ranks high on my list of delicious burgers. The forbidden rice was really good too and had a delicious sweet coconutty taste to it. Drinks were real cheap too - I got a four peaks hop knot for less than the price of a diet coke!   I'll definitely be going back.

